-- Growthpoint Sells $85 Million of Bonds as Demand for Offer Exceeds Supply
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2010-09-22T07:58:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/growthpoint-sells-85-million-of-bonds-as-demand-for-offer-exceeds-supply.html
Growthpoint Properties Ltd., the
largest South African real-estate investor, said it sold 600
million rand of bonds in an issue in which demand exceeded
supply by 4.3 times.  The company sold 200 million rand of three-month senior
unsecurted commercial paper at 33 basis points over the
equivalent Johannesburg Interbank Agreed Rate, Growthpoint said
in an e-mailed statement today. It also sold 400 million rand of
6-month commercial paper at 50 basis points over Jibar, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  